Scope and Usage
---------------

All alleles are described relative to a ReferenceSequence by way of the SimpleAllele.ReferenceCoordinate [see SimpleAllele](../simple_allele/index.html). Both the SimpleAllele position (or coordinates) and sequence at that postion are relative to the ReferenceSequence.


Context
-------

The ReferenceSequence resource is described by the following aspects:

* identifier (mandatory) - all users of reference sequences SHALL be sure of the identity of the reference sequence.
* referenceSequenceType (mandatory) - describes the kind of reference sequence.
* chromosome - the code representing one of the chromosomes, should be provided when the sequence represents a 'chromosome' (see [value set](/allele/implementation/value_set_list/reference_sequence_chromosome.html)).
* cdsStart - the start position of the coding sequence, when the reference sequence is a coding transcript. NOTE: Unlike reference coordinates, this is a 1-based index representing the position of the nucleotide.
* cdsEnd - the end position of the coding sequence, when the reference sequence is a coding transcript. NOTE: Unlike reference coordinates, this is a 1-based index representing the position of the nucleotide.
* gene - identifies the gene related to a 'gene' or 'transcript' reference sequence.
* referenceGenome - describes the genome build in which the chromosomal reference sequence is referenced.
* related reference sequences - other reference sequences that provide context about the primary reference sequence. See notes below for more info.

